Package com.ai.ASTCells

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ASTCell
    Represents a semantic meaning of a parsed NanoC syntax.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractASTCell
    Parent class of all concrete ASTCells.
    ActionASTCell
    Defines an Action nanoC non-terminal.
    addASTCell
    uses "+" or "-" operators to manipulate input cells
    AndASTCell
    Uses "&&" operator to manipulate BooleanASTCells that have a valid boolean value.
    ARefASTCell
    Used to represent an Array reference.
    AssignASTCell  
    BooleanASTCell
    A Singleton Class that Holds one instance of a FALSE BooleanASTCell.BooleanASTCell(boolean) and one instance of a TRUEBooleanASTCell.BooleanASTCell(boolean).
    CreatureASTCell
    Used to hold the information of a Creature definition.
    DivASTCell
    uses "/" operator to manipulate input NumberASTCells
    EQASTCell
    uses "==" operator to compare input of various ASTCells
    EqualASTCell  
    ExternalARefASTCell
    Used to represent and access data from an outside source.
    ExternalSymbolASTCell
    Used to represent and access data from an outside source.
    GTASTCell
    uses ">" operator to compare input of NumberASTCells
    GTEASTCell
    uses ">=" operator to compare input of NumberASTCells
    IFASTCell
    Node in the #AST structure representing an if statement.
    InternalSymbolASTCell
    Used to keep track of variables created during execution of a root syntax tree.
    LTASTCell
    uses "<" operator to compare input of NumberASTCells
    LTEASTCell
    uses "<=" operator to compare input of NumberASTCells
    MinusASTCell
    uses "-" operator to manipulate input NumberASTCells
    MultASTCell  
    NEQASTCell
    uses "==" operator to compare input of various ASTCells
    NilASTCell
    used to represent a null ASTCell with all null properties Uses Singleton design pattern since all nil cells are equivilent.
    NOTASTCell  
    NumberASTCell
    ASTCell type that holds a double value.
    OrASTCell  
    PlusASTCell
    uses "+" operator to manipulate input NumberASTCells
    PrefixASTCell
    Used to represent a Prefix value of a NUMBER cell.
    SequenceASTCell
    The type of ASTCell that holds the Master parsed Abstract Syntax tree.
    StoreASTCell
    This is the ASTCell responsible for creating an internal variable.
    StringASTCell
    A cell that holds a String value only.
    SubtractASTCell  
    SymbolASTCell  
    WhileASTCell
    Node in the #AST structure representing a while statement.
